cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on studying random gossip processes in communication models that describe the peer-to-peer networking functionality included in standard smartphone operating systems. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the efficiency and convergence of different gossip algorithms in the smartphone peer-to-peer setting. This involves analyzing the performance of algorithms, which is a key aspect of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper studies information spreading in peer-to-peer networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of social and information networks. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper introduces a new variation of the mobile telephone model that removes the synchronized round assumption, which involves studying the behavior of systems and control. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the spreading of information in peer-to-peer networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of information theory.
